------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  2.0.0      date: 02/3/2012 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

02/3/12
	Major new code release.  Code rewritten to support ultrasoft
	pseudopotentials with variable memory allocation.  Users can
	define storage used by ultrasoft calculation with the memory
	variable.  Other new features include non-linear core corrections,
	a randomize_vel command.
			
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.61.1      date: 08/30/2010 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

08/30
	Added Hubbard U output, warning that forces and stress not yet implemented.  
			
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.61.0      date: 08/26/2010 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

08/26
	Implemented DFT+U: added hubbard_u variable, and verified that
	code reproduces PWSCF results for FeO with k-points and spin.
		
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.60.0      date: 05/12/2010 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

05/12
	Added a run_timer variable, to let users set total run time limit.
	Code automatically decreases niter or nitscf when it detects the
	current values will prevent run command from completing in time.
		
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.59.2      date: 03/01/2010 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

03/01
	Fixed bug in Anderson ndim charge mixing with spin enabled: charge
	density not updating correctly on inactive spin contexts.
	
02/26
	Updated Makefile, rewrote printeig, printocc functions in
	Wavefunction to properly print from any combination of spin and
	k-points.
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.59.1      date: 02/19/2010 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

02/19
	New Makefile, which allows simultaneous compilation on different
	platforms from the same source directory.
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.59.0      date: 02/10/2010 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

02/10
	Implemented multidimensional Anderson accelerated charge mixing
	w. Tikhonov regularization from the Davis version of Qbox
	(1.50.4).  Currently only works w. nspin = 1.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.58.2      date: 02/09/2010 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

02/09
	Fixed bug where occupation in nspin > 1 case was insufficiently
	constrained, and could set occupations corresponding to
	non-integer total charge in each spin channel.  

02/09
	Changed Wavefunction.printocc and printeig to print out
	information for both spin channels, albeit on different processors
	(output may get mixed on some systems).  Needs to be rewritten.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.58.1      date: 01/29/2010 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

01/29
	Wrote qb-nruns-list, which allows user to input a single argument,
	namely a file containing a list of input filenames, to avoid the
	mpirun argument character limit that gets hit with large numbers
	of input files.
	
01/26
	Added warning message when scf convergence threshold set but ionic
	iteration completes without triggering it.  Useful for monitoring long MD runs. 
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.58.0      date: 01/25/2010 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

01/25
	Change save/load binary formats (for both states and dump formats)
	to no longer include filename as first line of the file (needed to
	get around bug in BG/L xlc compiler, but makes portability
	difficult, as filename assumed to stay of fixed length).
	
