	Fixed bug with new method of storing mixed charge density between
	ionic iterations when cell dynamics are on, which can cause
	non-integer electronic charge.  Now, stored mixing is not used
	when cell_dyn != LOCKED.  Also, there's a check that rhog size
	doesn't change between ionic iterations (i.e. ref_cell is being
	used)
	
