------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.37.1      date:  5/5/2008
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5/5
	Implemented a Hugoniostat to automatically adjust temperature to
	keep system on the hugoniot line, defined by E-E_0 +
	0.5*(V-V_0)(P-P_0) = 0.
		
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.37.0      date:  4/16/2008
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4/16
	Modified PSDAWavefunctionStepper.C to be more stable and converge
	faster for metals.  Partially and unoccupied states were
	dominating the calculation of the extrapolation parameter once the
	system started to become converged, leading to saturation of theta
	and an effectively constant acceleration.  Reweighting the
	extrapolation with an occupation prefactor has made the algorithm
	more stable and significantly faster for metals: twice as fast as
	the old PSDA for a disordered 108-atom gold calculation, and five
	times as fast as PSD.
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.36.5      date:  4/10/2008
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4/10
	Implemented the PBEsol functional, a modified PBE-GGA designed to more
	accurately capture exchange-correlation effects for solids and
	surfaces than standard PBE.  PBEsol is expected to do worse than
	PBE for individual atoms and molecules.  See PRL 100, 136406
	(2008).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.36.4      date:  4/7/2008
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4/7
	Changed Sample and save/load commands (-states, -dump) to store
	mixed charge density to prevent discontinuity on checkpointing for
	systems sensitive to charge mixing paramters, e.g. transition
	metals.

4/1
	Changed PSDAWavefunctionStepper to output Anderson extrapolation
	theta, but only for first k-point.
	
2/26
	Changed step function in EnthalpyFunctional to be symmetric about rho=threshold.
	
2/21
	Changed text output to use a Context.oncoutpe, which allows one to
	define a non-zero process for printing output.
	
1/21
	Fixed bug in threshold_force, due to EnergyFunctional.energy
	zeroing fion in calls with compute_forces=false.
	
