------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.32.0      date:  4/11/2007
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

4/11
	Implemented classical atoms and empirical interactions.  The short-term 
	goal is to allow for an atomistic pressure medium for nanostructures, 
	but the implementation was designed to allow for general interactions.  
	
3/27
	Reimplemented fermi_temp variable to maintain backward
	compatibility with older Qbox input files and Francois' version of
	the code.  Set fermi_temp reads in smearing width in Kelvin and
	converts it to Ry.
	
3/14
	dt_inv set to 0.0 when dt=0.0, to avoid singularity in wfv and
	divergence in subsequent run commands.  This bug only occurs when
	one runs with dt=0.0 to relax wave function and print forces, and
	then sets dt > 0.0 to relax atoms in the same input file. 
	
	
