2/17
	Rewrote Basis and KpointCmd to store k-points in crystal
	coordinates instead of Cartesian so that variable cell
	calculations still use the appropriate k-point grid.
   
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.31.4      date:  2/15/2007
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

2/15
	Added occupation and eigenvalue info to save/load -states when
	nempty > 0.
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.31.3      date:  2/13/2007
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

2/13
	Fixed bug in save -states, where only real part of wave function
	was being saved.  
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.31.2      date:  2/12/2007
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

2/12
	Rewrote load/save -states to Fourier transform wave function to
	real space before saving.
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.31.1      date:  2/8/2007
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

2/8
	Implemented load/save -states to allow for restarting on arbitrary
	context shapes.  (Previous checkpoint load/save support required
	restarting on an identical parallel layout.)

	Added save/load -xml switch, to allow checkpointing with original
	Qbox xml format.  Can only be used with one k-point.
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.31.0      date:  1/24/2007
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

1/24
	Added complex linear algebra support to routines used by PSDA, to
	allow one to use PSDA with k-points.  
    
	Improved automatic Ewald parameter selection.  Parameters are now
	chosen so that both real-space and reciprocal space sums are
	well-converged, and small enough that all ionic charge is enclosed
	within cell.  Reciprocal sum threshold scaled by rcps/zval,
	similar to approach used by PWSCF, after testing showed a single
	threshold was insufficient for different species.
	
1/23
	Changed Symmetry object to use double arguments instead of ints,
	to allow for non-cubic operations.  

12/22
	Added saveden command, with rudimentary text output.  Still need
	to add binary output, and density loading capability.
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.30.0      date:  12/20/2006
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

12/20
	Added iprint variable to control output of eigenvalues and
	occupation numbers.  

	Fixed symmetry-averaging of forces for non-cubic cells (error in
	conversion to crystal coordinates before applying transform).  

	Changed dt_inv to 1E20 when dt=0.0 and compute_forces=true to
	prevent divergence.
    
	

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.29.0      date:  12/08/2006
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

12/8
	Forces with f-projectors are now working and have been tested with
	a 2-atom tantalum calculation.  
	

10/20
 	Added default values to ExtStress.  

	Added simple thresholds to scf and non-scf electronic iteration
	loops, with input variables scf_threshold and nonscf_threshold.
      
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.28.0      date:  9/19/2006
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

9/19
	Forces are now averaged over symmetry-equivalent atoms, when
	symmetry command is used.  Tests against PWSCF show agreement
	within 3.0E-7 a.u.

7/14	
	Added savesys command to allow for MD restart on platforms without
	xml support (e.g. BG/L)
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.27.0      date:  6/14/2006
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

6/14    
	Methfessel-Paxton charge smearing implemented.  Charge smearing
	now enabled with the smearing keyword, and the width set with the
	smearing_width keyword (in Ry).  The fermi_temp keyword has been
	disabled.

	To run with Fermi smearing:
	  set smearing fermi
	  set smearing_width [fermi temperature in Rydbergs]
	To run with Methfessel-Paxton smearing, with four terms in the expansion:
	  set smearing gaussian 4
	  set smearing_width [width in Ry]
	To run with simple Gaussian smearing
	  set smearing gaussian 0
	  set smearing_width [width in Ry]
	
5/17	
	Eigenvalue printing for multiple k-points now synchronized to
	print from pe 0 to prevent overlapping output from other
	contexts.  

5/3	
	Added reshape_context variable, to toggle automatic reshaping of
	context for square matrix operations in SlaterDet.gram and
	Wavefunction.diag.  This can improve performance for very
	rectangular contexts on large numbers of processors,
	e.g. BlueGene/L.  

4/5	
	Added charge_mixing keywords, to allow user to disable Anderson
	mixing and use simple mixing instead.  
	
	
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
version:  1.26.0      date:  3/24/2006
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

3/24    
	Charge symmetrization implemented, though not fully tested yet.
	
3/21   	
	Symmetry command added, and Symmetry and SymmetrySet objects created.

	
